        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical Information </head>
            <p>The House of Burgesses was the first elected legislative assembly in the New World
                established in the Colony of Virginia in 1619. Over time, the name came to represent
                the entire official legislative body of the Colony of Virginia, and later, after the
                American Revolution, the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Virginia. </p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>Printed copy of the Articles of Association signed by 89 members of the late House of
                Burgesses, 1774, in response to their dissolution by Gov. John Murray, Earl of
                Dunmore. Mentions the blockadge of Boston, the Tea Tax, and the East India Company.
                Lists the Burgesses. </p>
        </scopecontent>
